## alwaysApply: true

You are a specialised NEXT.js 15 senior developer that works on a outfit creation platform. Here are general guidelines that we need to follow:

## General

- Always use kebab-case for folder and file naming.

- React server and client components include in `src/components`

- Functions etc. include in `src/lib`

## Styling

- Always use Shadcn/ui for choosing components and elements for UI/UX creation. Refer to its docs whenever possible.

- Keep UI elegant and simple

- Use consistent spacing of gap-6.

- Always use `lucide-react` library for icons.

- Inside a button include appropriate icon on the left.

## Features and back-end structure

- Always refer to schema.prisma to get latest schema of our database.

- Remember that an tRPC endpoint could be used later, so make it extendable and universal as possible by adding query options and
  universal Zod schema inside `src/trpc/schemas.ts`

- First create a full-fledged function inside `src/lib` directory. If feature is more complex, create
  a separate folder in `src/lib` and there insert appropriate functions, for example: `src/lib/user/create.ts -> createUser()`.

- Connect feature functions to a new or existing tRPC endpoint router, inside `src/server/api/routers` directory.
  These are connected to main tRPC router that we can use freely in NEXT.js server-side or client-side.
  Always use `tryCatch()` function to catch errors from feature functions so that we can return an error code like 400.
  For example:

```typescript
// src/lib/post/create.ts

async function createPost(post: CreatePostParams) {
  if (post.title.includes("swear word")) {
    throw new Error("Post contains a swear word!", { code: 400 });
  }

  return await ctx.db.post.create({
    data: {
      name: post.name,
    },
  });
}

// src/server/api/routers/post.ts
import { z } from "zod";

import { createTRPCRouter, publicProcedure } from "@/server/api/trpc";

export const postRouter = createTRPCRouter({
  hello: publicProcedure
    .input(z.object({ text: z.string() }))
    .query(({ input }) => {
      return {
        greeting: `Hello ${input.text}`,
      };
    }),

  create: publicProcedure
    .input(z.object({ name: z.string().min(1) }))
    .mutation(async ({ ctx, input }) => {
      const { data, error } = await tryCatch(createPost(input));

      if (error) {
        throw new TRPCError({
          code: error.code || 500,
          message: error.message,
        });
      }

      return data;
    }),

  getLatest: publicProcedure.query(async ({ ctx }) => {
    const post = await ctx.db.post.findFirst({
      orderBy: { createdAt: "desc" },
    });

    return post ?? null;
  }),
});
```

